`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `void triggerActionHaptic(action)` pattern is idiomatic TypeScript for "fire and forget async in sync context" — it explicitly discards the Promise (silencing `no-floating-promises` linters) while keeping `dispatchAction` synchronous. The alternative (making `dispatchAction` async) would cascade through all callers with no benefit.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

